# PropPredict — Cursor rules

## Project overview

PropPredict is a white-label prediction markets platform for prop firms. The stack is:

- **Backend**: FastAPI (`backend/`), PostgreSQL, Redis, LMSR internal markets
- **Frontend**: Next.js (`frontend/`), fortraders.com-inspired trader UI
- **Multi-tenant**: firm-scoped branding via DB-backed tenant config

## Polymarket integration

Polymarket CLOB integration is a first-class part of this project.

- **Package**: `backend/integrations/polymarket/`
  - `PolymarketClient` — async wrapper around `py-clob-client-v2`
  - `PolymarketService` — caching, normalization, search, health checks
  - `rate_limiter.py` — outbound request throttling
- **Config**: `PP_POLYMARKET_*` env vars in `backend/app/core/config.py` (see `.env.example`)
- **API routes**: `backend/app/api/routes/polymarket.py` (`/api/polymarket/*`)
- **Hybrid markets**: `backend/app/runtime/hybrid_markets.py` merges internal LMSR + Polymarket feeds
- **Trading API**: `GET /api/v1/trading/markets?source=internal|polymarket|all`
- **Frontend**: Polymarket cards, three-way source toggle (All / Internal / Polymarket), `/markets` explorer
- **Docs**: `backend/integrations/polymarket/README.md`, Super Admin `/platform/integrations`

When adding market features, preserve the unified market shape (`source: "internal" | "polymarket"`) and keep UI consistent with internal `MarketCard` styling.

## Conventions

- Match existing code style; keep diffs focused
- Backend tests: `cd backend && pytest tests/ -q`
- Frontend build: `cd frontend && npm run build`
- Branch prefix for agent work: `cursor/<name>-224f`
